  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nThe `Escrow.deposit` function emits a `Deposited` event, which is not stated in its doc.\r\nSimilarly, the `Escrow.withdraw` function emits a `Withdrawn` event, which is not stated in its doc either.\r\n\r\nA potential fix could be adding \"Emits a {Deposited} event\" to the doc of `Escrow.deposit`, and adding \"Emits a {Withdrawn} event\" to `Escrow.withdraw`.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/fcf35e5722847f5eadaaee052968a8a54d03622a/contracts/utils/escrow/Escrow.sol#L41\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/fcf35e5722847f5eadaaee052968a8a54d03622a/contracts/utils/escrow/Escrow.sol#L61\r\n\r\nThese events can also transitively emit in the functions `PullPayment._asyncTransfer` and `PullPayment.withdrawPayments`, because they call `Escrow.deposit` and `Escrow.withdraw` respectively.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/fcf35e5722847f5eadaaee052968a8a54d03622a/contracts/security/PullPayment.sol#L68\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/fcf35e5722847f5eadaaee052968a8a54d03622a/contracts/security/PullPayment.sol#L48\r\n\r\nCould you please check it?\r\n\r\nThanks.",
